      "sentence_index": 0,
      "text": "This paper studies the characteristics of representations and their roles in neural network expressiveness.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HJeleGmwnQ",
      "sentence_index": 1,
      "text": "The results  are overall not very impressive.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_motivation-impact",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HJeleGmwnQ",
      "sentence_index": 2,
      "text": "1. There are many characteristics of representations such as scaling, permutation, covariance, correlation, sparsity, dead units, rank.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_fact",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HJeleGmwnQ",
      "sentence_index": 3,
      "text": "The papers discusses some (not surprising) theoretical properties relating to scaling, permutation, covariance, correlation, while making less efforts on the more interesting characteristics  sparsity, dead units, rank, mutual information.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_substance",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HJeleGmwnQ",
      "sentence_index": 4,
      "text": "Only some heuristic results are obtained for them without rigorous theory.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HJeleGmwnQ",
      "sentence_index": 5,
      "text": "It would be better if these heuristic arguments can be formed as theorems as well.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_request",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-request_result",
      "aspect": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HJeleGmwnQ",
      "sentence_index": 6,
      "text": "2. Probably the most interesting experimental finding of this paper is that the mutual information between z and output is constant, while the one between z and input strongly depends on the regularizers.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HJeleGmwnQ",
      "sentence_index": 7,
      "text": "That is, the dependence between z and y does not vary with regularizers but the one between z and x does.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_fact",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "HJeleGmwnQ",
      "sentence_index": 8,
      "text": "Is this a coincidence or a general phenomenon? Is there a theoretical explanation?",
